Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees and put a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to boil for the rigatoni.

Cut the @British chicken thighs{6} into 1cm thick strips. Place in a #baking dish{} and season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @ground black pepper{a good grind}. Mix well.

Dissolve the @chicken stock pot{1} in 200ml of boiling water and pour this over the chicken. Cover your dish with #foil{} and pop in your oven for ~{25%minutes}. The chicken is cooked when the centre is no longer pink!

While your chicken cooks prepare the veggies. Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and slice into thin half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. 

> Tip: Use a garlic press if you have one!

Chop the top and bottom off the @courgettes{2} and cut in half lengthways. Chop the courgettes into half moon shapes 1cm thick. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into 1cm slices.

Pop four-fifths of the @rigatoni pasta{400%g} into the boiling water (you don't need to use the whole packet) and cook for ~{10%minutes}. When your pasta is cooked, drain and return to your pot. Mix in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with a good grind of @ground black pepper{a good grind} and @salt{pinch}.

Heat a #frying pan{} over medium heat and add @oil{1%tbsp}. Cook the red onions for ~{3%minutes} and then add the courgettes and peppers. Sprinkle in the @Provencal herbs{1/2} and cook for another ~{3%minutes}. Add the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute} more and then pour in the @tomato passata{2}. Cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Tear half of the @basil{3} leaves. Mix the basil into your veggies and get ready to assemble your pasta bake! Switch your grill to its highest setting.

Pop your rigatoni into the bottom of a deep #ovenproof dish{} and top with your cooked chicken and the cooking juices. Spoon your provençal veggies on top and then cover with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{6%tbsp}. Pop under your grill for ~{3%minutes} or until the cheese is bubbling and golden. Sprinkle over the remaining basil leaves and tuck in.